The {{transformer}} plugin modules added in Confluence 4.0 provide a great way to update/inject page content on the fly.  

The current interface only provides a {{transform}} method which takes a {{Reader}} object and returns a {{String}}.  In many cases the transformer will not actually have any transforming to do, but it still needs to parse the entire page content from the {{Reader}} and return it as a {{String}}.

This could be improved by providing a way for the transformer to tell the calling code if it should be run. This will prevent the entire page content needing to be parsed one more time if the conditions for running can be determined before hand from the context.  This could be done through a new interface method, or by adding condition parameters to the module config (like web-ui items).

